sector.narrative:
Implementing Bangladesh Delta Plan 2100 concerns bringing the long term adaptation to climate change and related water governance approach with multi-sectoral strategic planning and investment ambitions into practice. This means preparing and acting upon the following implementation activities:
- preparing necessary institutional development and arrangements to prepare a dedicated Delta Wing under GED and national Delta Governance Council;
- increasing connective capacity of involved institutions and implementing agencies; participation of stakeholders; 
-  knowledgemanagement and learning by improving the Information Portal and by additional studies;
- increasing the funding capacity for investements considering funding 1) by GoB, Development Partners and IFI's; 2) by PPP investments; 3) by Green Climate Fund;
- adapting the natural systems and processes in the Delta according to BDP2100 strategies and proposed projects. This is done by River Basin Management and basin wise programming with a dedicated decision support system.
